#: _posts/2023-01-31-quarkus-3-7-released.adoc
msgid "Java 17 is the new baseline"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2023-01-31-quarkus-3-7-released.adoc
msgid "As was announced at https://quarkus.io/blog/java-17/[the end of November], you will need a Java 17+ runtime (using Java 21 is encouraged!) to run Quarkus 3.7 applications."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2023-01-31-quarkus-3-7-released.adoc
msgid ""
"When we released Quarkus 3.0, we announced that Java 11 support was deprecated and would go away at some point.\n"
"This is the time."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2023-01-31-quarkus-3-7-released.adoc
msgid "Most of the Java ecosystem is moving to Java 17 as the baseline so it wasn't sustainable for Quarkus to support Java 11 much longer."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2023-01-31-quarkus-3-7-released.adoc
msgid ""
"If your Java 17 migration is ongoing, you can upgrade to the latest 3.6 but keep in mind that 3.6.9 released today is the latest 3.6.\n"
"If you are stuck with Java 11 for some time, we recommend using Quarkus 3.2 LTS as it will be maintained longer."
msgstr ""

